<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-08T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-08T03:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/3–850: Circular
                                telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular
                                        Offices</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d392fn1">Sent to Damascus; repeated to
                                    Beirut, Baghdad, Cairo, and Jidda.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-08T03:00:00-05:00">March
                                        8, 1950—3 a. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> Tel Aviv reports high Israeli
                                official disturbed by recent Reuters report that Syrian <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> has declared his Govt is
                                considering closing Syrian frontiers with Jordan if 5-year agreement
                                Jordan-Israel becomes effective, and that other Arab Govts now
                                conferring on what action to take if this agreement reached.
                                Comment.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>